headlines.description: — Kai Havertz’s late finish sealed a nervy 1-0 win for Chelsea over resurgent Newcastle on Sunday, providing a rare distraction from the uncertainty surrounding the club's future.
headlines.shortLinkText: Havertz's late goal gives Chelsea 1-0 win over Newcastle

headlines.description: Wolves defender Conor Coady scored the only goal as Everton's Premier League relegation fears deepened following a 1-0 home defeat.
headlines.shortLinkText: Everton relegation fears grow after Wolves loss

headlines.description: Joe Gelhardt came off the bench to score a stoppage-time winner as Leeds secured a 2-1 victory over Norwich City on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marsch earns 1st Leeds win after last-gasp goal

headlines.description: Watford striker Cucho Hernandez bagged a brace and kept his club's survival hopes alive after a 2-1 victory at Southampton.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hernandez brace helps Watford edge past Saints

events.name: Aston Villa at West Ham United

headlines.description: Ukrainian Andriy Yarmolenko and Spanish midfielder Pablo Fornals scored a goal each as West Ham defeated Aston Villa 2-1 at home on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Emotional Yarmolenko sees West Ham edge Villa

headlines.description: Arsenal continued their fine form and returned to the top four with an impressive 2-0 win over Leicester City at the Emirates Stadium on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arsenal up to fourth after win over Leicester
